Def ensures numerical stability (e.g., `cbDecay` clipped to 0.05..10.0s).\n- The `cbDampCutoff` formula provides a musically useful transition from \"bright\" to \"woody\" resonance.\n- SC-side tests include automated RMS and FFT-based magnitude checks for objective verification.\n\n## Issues Found\n- None.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is solid and well-verified. The candidate hardening checks regarding `bootstrap_identity` were also verified to be pre-existing and correctly wired in both `daemon.py` and `cypherclaw_daemon.py`.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-002@20260425t183959zd-verify.md"}}
