sdp/verification/t-014@20260427t001208z-verify.md:122:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-27T17:56:44.626Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777312604626_0","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-014 @sdp/logs/Verify_T-014_20260427T001208Z_1777312500.log\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-04-27\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/composer_hook.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/duet_composer.py`\n- `tests/test_generation_composer_hook.py`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation of `_should_queue_now(mode, mood, learning)` correctly enforces all three requested gates:\n1. **Rate Gate**: It enforces a 30-minute cooldown by checking `last_generation_enqueued_at` from the `learning` state (or `last_enqueued_at` override).\n2. **Antipattern Gate**: It returns `False` if `sampler_dominating` is reported in the `learning` state.\n3. **Budget Gate**: It returns `False` if the daily budget remaining is ≤ $0.50.\n\nIt also correctly handles the cold start case (returning `True` if no prior enqueue time is found) and the quiet work gate (`working_ambience` mode with `arc_payoff < 0.4`).\n\n## Completeness\nAll acceptance criteria have been met:\n- 30-minute cooldown: implemented via `MIN_GENERATION_INTERVAL_SECONDS = 30.0 * 60.0`.\n- Sampler antipattern check: implemented via `_sampler_dominating_reported(learning)`.\n- Budget check: implemented via `remaining <= MIN_DAILY_BUDGET_REMAINING_USD` (0.50).\n- Cold start: implemented via `if last_enqueued_at is None: return True`.\n- Working ambience gate: implemented via `arc_payoff < 0.4`.\n- Tests: `tests/test_generation_composer_hook.py` covers all branches including cold start, rate gate (via learning), budget gate, and antipattern gate.\n\n## Consistency\nThe implementation follows existing patterns in the codebase, such as using `_mapping_value` and `_float_value` helpers for flexible state access and maintaining the module-level timestamp in `duet_composer.py`.\n\n## Security\nNo security vulnerabilities or leaked secrets identified. The implementation uses local state and deterministic hashing for request building.\n\n## Quality\nCode is clean, idiomatic, and well-tested. The integration into `duet_composer.py` correctly threads the module-level state into the `learning` dictionary to fix the throttle regression.\n\n## Issues Found\nNone.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is solid and addresses the regression noted in T-013. The tests are comprehensive.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-014 @20260427t001208z-verify.md"}}
