specs/t-022@20260416t054258z-spec.md:1:# Task T-022 Specification: Build SuperCollider recipe references without coupling tests to live audio
specs/t-022@20260416t054258z-spec.md:4:The project needs a comprehensive set of SuperCollider recipe references to support curriculum exercises. These recipes must be discoverable from existing curriculum documentation but tested without relying on live audio server execution, which can cause flaky tests and coupling issues.
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:27:8. **Cross-voice coupling** — shared affective-state bus per voice family; voices react to each other's expression intensity
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:283:- Each synthdef adds internal LFOs and EnvGens controlled by these parameters. Where the underlying synthesis can't naturally support a modulator (e.g. tremolo on a granular-only voice), the modulator is implemented at the post-voice send level via amplitude or pitch modulation on the FX send.
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:287:- **Scene-phase intensity multiplier** (§7.4) applied at gesture application time to modulator depths.
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:288:- **Contour-aware dynamics** — composer's note-emitter computes contour position for each note (peak / ascending / descending / static / valley) using a sliding window of adjacent notes; passes `dynamics_multiplier` and `attack_shape` in the OSC event. No model; simple slope arithmetic.
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:294:  - `scene_phase_scaling.py` (multiplier lookup)
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:309:### Feature 8 — Cross-Voice Coupling
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:314:- A shared control bus `affective_state_bus` (a single SuperCollider control bus) holds a float in `[0.0, 1.0]` — the current "ensemble affect."
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:316:- Each voice reads the bus and applies a coupling multiplier to its own modulator depths: `effective_vib_depth = nominal_vib_depth * (1 + coupling_strength * affective_state)`. `coupling_strength` is a per-voice parameter (default 0.5, configurable per voice).
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:317:- The bus has a slow-decay built in so the affective state doesn't lock high — when no voice is contributing intensity, the bus decays toward 0 over ~5 seconds.
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:321:- `my-claw/tools/expression/affective_bus.py` (writer-side)
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:322:- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/coupling/affective_bus_router.scd` (SuperCollider-side reader)
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:325:- All voice synthdefs (read coupling multiplier from bus)
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:334:- When the counter exceeds threshold (default 0.7), the voice applies a fatigue multiplier to subsequent notes' expression parameters: `effective_param = nominal_param * (1 - 0.5 * normalize(fatigue_counter))`.
